<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>take one’s stand • take the stand</xh5><p> <i>take one’s stand—</i>take one’s place or position: The players, except one, <u>take their stand</u> at one side, and one stands at the other side in front of them.</p><p><i>take the stand—</i>1. <i>(U.S. legal)</i> come into the witness box to give testimony: The judge next asked the defendant to <u>take the stand</u>. 2. take one’s position on an elevated platform (as a speaker, etc.): So many people roll their eyes when they hear a girl singer is about to <u>take the stand</u>.</p> </entry>
